01/02/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The leader of the main opposition party Social Democratic Party (SDP), former Prime Minister Ivica Racan, announced on Wednesday (January 31st) that he has been diagnosed abroad with an atypical tumour and will leave public life for now.
He added that whether he returns will depend on the outcome of surgery he will be undergoing soon.
His deputy, Zeljka Antunovic, is taking over the SDP post.
(Vecernji list - 01/02/07;
HRT, HINA - 31/01/07)
